shows.title: Trainer Games
shows.plot_overview: Hosted by Emmy-nominated TV host, actress and celebrity fitness entrepreneur Amanda Kloots (The Talk, Blue Bloods), Trainer Games chronicles ten elite competitors — Chari Hawkins, Chris Griffiths, Dan Holguin, Darryl Williams, Divinity Gaines, Heather Gollnick, Nick Ullman, Nikki Keys, Kori Sampson, and Yanessa Navarro — as they fight their way through treacherous challenges set against stunning backdrops of Mauritius, an island in the Indian Ocean known for its adventure landscapes.

shows.title: Blue Skies
shows.plot_overview: National Park Investigator Jodi Larsen and a lost dog named Blue team up to solve mysteries in the wilderness, forging an unexpected bond amidst danger and healing.

shows.title: The Floor
shows.plot_overview: British adaptation of the Dutch game show where 81 quiz fanatics face off in quiz duels on a giant LED floor divided into 81 equal squares, each representing its own field of knowledge. The goal is to conquer the entire floor and take home a huge cash prize.

shows.title: The Cult of the Real Housewife
shows.plot_overview: Ex-members and family speak out about The Real Housewives of Salt Lake City star Mary Cosby and the troubling inner workings of Faith Temple Pentecostal Church.

shows.title: Impractical Roommates
shows.plot_overview: The series involves an anxious, careful, and kind of a "neat-freak" rat named Ratty, and a big strong fearless and trustworthy pigeon named Stu, as they both live together in an apartment, sometimes they do things their own way in town, but they are still friends either way.

shows.title: Suddenly Amish
shows.plot_overview: Six non-Amish individuals on a rare journey leave behind their modern "English" lifestyle and step into a deeply traditional Amish community in Lancaster, Pennsylvania.
